24/02/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Prosecutors have issued an arrest warrant for Simeon Vilovski, a close associate of Bishop Artemije, who was recently removed from his post in Kosovo over the suspected embezzlement of millions of euros in aid and government money. Dusica Ristic, spokesperson for the High Court, explained on Tuesday (February 23rd) that authorities are unable to locate Vilovski, who is suspected of embezzling 350,000 euros intended for the reconstruction of monasteries in Kosovo. (Beta, B92, AP - 23/02/10)
